 content is restricted and the user may not access the content without documented requirements  If you have a business need to access these sites  please refer to General Order 50  to document the access required  VMI subscribes to a service that dynamically blocks access to legitimate sites that may become infected  Once the infection remediation has completed  the service enables access again  Web content categories affected and their descriptions are  Categories IPC Action Post IPC Action Barracks Description Adult and Pornography Block Warn Sexually explicit material for the purpose of arousing a sexual or prurient interest  Adult products including sex toys  CD ROMs  and videos  Online groups  including newsgroups and forums  that are sexually explicit in nature  Erotic stories and textual descriptions of sexual acts  Adult services including videoconferencing  escort services  and strip clubs  Sexually explicit art  Bot Nets Block     Block These are URLs  typically IP addresses  which are determined to be part of a Bot network  from which network attacks are launched  Attacks may include SPAM messages  DOS  SQL injections  proxy jacking  and other unsolicited contacts  Confirmed Spam Sources Block Block A confirmed source of junk email or unsolicited bulk email with the possible malicious intent of sending users to phishing web sites  or sites hosting malware  Hacking Warn Warn Illegal or questionable access to or the use of communications equipment software  Development and distribution of programs that may allow compromise of networks and systems  Avoidance of licensing and fees for computer programs and other systems  Hate and Racism Warn Warn Sites that support content and languages or hate crime and racism such as Nazi  neo Nazi  Ku Klux Klan  etc  Illegal Block Block Criminal activity  how not to get caught  copyright and intellectual property violations  etc  Keyloggers   Monitoring Warn Warn Downloads and discussion of software agents that track a user s keystrokes or monitor their web surfing habits  Malware Sites Block Block Malicious content including executables  drive by infection sites  malicious scripts  viruses  trojans  and code  Online Gambling Block Warn Gambling or lottery web sites that invite the use of real or virtual money  Information or advice for placing wagers  participating in lotteries  gambling  or running numbers  Virtual casinos and offshore gambling ventures  Sports picks and betting pools  Virtual sports and fantasy leagues that offer large rewards or request significant wagers  Hotel and Resort sites that do not enable gambling on the site are categorized in Travel or Local Information  Peer to Peer Warn Warn Peer to peer clients and access  Includes torrents  music download programs  Phishing and other frauds Block Block Phishing  pharming  and other sites that pose as a reputable site  usually to harvest personal information from a user  These sites are typically quite short lived  so examples do not last long  Proxy Avoidance   Anonymizers Block Block Proxy servers and other methods to gain access to URLs in any way that bypasses URL filtering or monitoring  Web based translation sites that circumvent filtering  SPAM URLs Block Block URLs contained in SPAM  Spyware   Adware Block Warn Spyware or Adware sites that provide or promote information gathering or tracking that is unknown to  or without the explicit consent of  the end user or the organization  also unsolicited advertising popups and programs that may be installed on a user s computer  Unconfirmed Spam Sources Warn Warn An unconfirmed source of junk email or unsolicited bulk email with the possible malicious intent of sending users to phishing web sites  or sites hosting malware  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevan